OL,4,Cand is silent prayer banned?
OL,6,FThe guidance refers to a 2022 Supreme
OL,7,FCourt ruling regarding safe access
OL,8,Fzones in Northern Ireland, where the
OL,9,Fcourt considered silent prayer to be
OL,10,Famong the acts which "were capable of
OL,11,Ffalling within the scope of the
OL,12,Fstatutory provision".
OL,14,FIt states that "a person who carries
OL,15,Fout any of these activities within a
OL,16,Fsafe access zone will not necessarily
OL,17,Fcommit a criminal offence".
