OL,6,F"Prosecutors will need to consider not
OL,7,Fonly all the facts and circumstances
OL,8,Fof the particular conduct but also the
OL,9,Fcontext in which the conduct takes
OL,10,Fplace."
OL,12,FIn considering cases, it states that
OL,13,Fprosecutors should clearly identify
OL,14,F"the overt act that gives rise to the
OL,15,Foffence" and evidence "from which the
OL,16,Frequisite intent or recklessness can
OL,17,Fbe inferred".
